The paper discusses the challenges of SLAM in dynamic and changing environments, which is a common problem in robotics (cs.RO). The authors also mention the importance of visual features and pose estimation, which are related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a benchmarking metric for evaluating the robustness and accuracy of pose estimation, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the deployment and operation of service robots, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
